race.comment: FINE STAR (4) is a progressive filly who got off the mark last time at Belmont Park when storming home to score. No tougher here and expected to go close again. SUPIDO EXPRESS (2) resumed at Bunbury and tried to lead throughout but was swamped late for a close-up third. Fitter and will take catching. DOMINATUS (8) made his debut in a Belmont Park maiden and ran on well for a solid fifth. Goes up a grade but has good upside and no surprise if he ran on into the finish at odds. HEDAWOOD (1) has raced twice so far and after winning on debut charged home late to finish runner-up. Has a wide draw but Pike goes aboard and should be charging again. KIMBERLEY CURRENCY (5) has been consistent since a win four back and will give a sight on speed.
